Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that, I'd like to introduce\NDr. David Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.76,0:00:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We always start with Gloria and\NExcelsius Theo. Glory to thee, oh Lord
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.43,0:00:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,most high.\NAll right. If I can recover from that,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.28,0:00:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we will have a lecture.\NI forgot what the lecture was about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.71,0:00:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,today.\NSo, I brought this thing here
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell me what it's about.\NWhat's the name of the lecture?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.60,0:00:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, so it isn't just me.\N>> It's It's true. faith, uh, truth and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.60,0:01:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> faith, reason.\N>> Well, I don't know what we'll find out
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.32,0:01:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what the what the name of this speech is\Nlater.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.43,0:01:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've got the How many people here\Nare new?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.56,0:01:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here are new? Yes.\NOkay. Not a lot. Just a few. So for the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.28,0:01:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,few we'll just recapitulate some of the\Nmost basic slides to give you an
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.28,0:01:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,orientation or a reorientation\Nuh to the entire subject. And um so
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.43,0:01:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,let's start with uh\Nuh this is the the basic slide to which
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.88,0:01:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,we refer you know the calibrated levels\Nof consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.15,0:01:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and um h how they arose in the first\Nplace
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.36,0:01:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh was interesting\Nbecause um we were studying I had a big
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.28,0:02:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,clinic back east and we were studying\Num all the things that could help
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.04,0:02:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,patients who were very desperate. They'd\Nbeen everywhere in the world, nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.39,0:02:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,had helped. So, we were looking at every\Ndiagnostic and healing modality,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.48,0:02:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,many of which uh traditional science poo\Npooed, you know, cerebral allergy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.48,0:02:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,functional hypoglycemia,\Nthings that were of critical importance
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.31,0:02:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to the patients we saw and were not part\Nof traditional medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.12,0:02:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the things we looked at was\Nkinesiology and muscle testing and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.28,0:02:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,various things like that.\NAnd and the first thing that was
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.80,0:02:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,impressive about it was if you take a\Nnaive person, let's say you take a naive
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,person and you tell them to look at the\Nfluorescent light and to hold tell them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,hold your arm out and resist\Nand then you push down. If they look at
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.31,0:03:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the fluorescent light, their arm goes\Nweak.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.92,0:03:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's standard. Or if you put a\Npesticide next to the solar plexus,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.12,0:03:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,their arm goes weak.\NSo I was going to give a lecture on it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.20,0:03:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to the staff at the clinic. We had a\Npretty big staff, about 50 people or
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.00,0:03:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,100, I guess. Anyway, a lot. And uh so I\Nneeded some volunteers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.44,0:03:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said, "Who wants to volunteer?" And\Nthere were some people standing around
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.59,0:03:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had a attitudinal healing center\Nthere for hopeless diseases based on a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.59,0:03:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,course of miracles. And uh so a couple\Nof them were standing around and I said,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.56,0:03:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,"Come on over here. I want to\Ndemonstrate something." So I said, "All
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.23,0:03:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,right, look at the fluorescent lights."\NAnd I pressed down and their arm did not
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak. What\Nmakes everybody's arm go weak? So I held
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.31,0:03:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,pesticides over their solar plexus and I\Npressed down and they did not go weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.04,0:04:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So something about these people had\Ntransformed their whole energy balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.68,0:04:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And with further investigation, we found\Nout that by the time you get up to about
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.15,0:04:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,lesson 75 in a course of miracles,\Nuh you become immune to negative
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.59,0:04:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,stimuli. They no longer blow out your\Nacupuncture meridians.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.12,0:04:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a very important discovery.\NThen then uh it came to me from uh other
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.80,0:04:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,places\Nthat you could calibrate it an actual
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.08,0:04:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,scale of relativity.\NAnd by using the same technique uh we
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.91,0:04:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,went up the traditional chain of being\Nstarting out at the bottom is hatred and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.60,0:04:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,despair and and all the\Nso we started out with the chain of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.19,0:04:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,being and we found uh that all things\Nlike shame and hate and all calibrated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.91,0:05:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,way down at the bottom and the emotion\Ngoing with that is humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.32,0:05:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we constructed this is the\Nclassic chain of being uh it's in many
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.96,0:05:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,uh psychological\Nstudies and traditional spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.24,0:05:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,traditions\Nand we found a correlation between your
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.75,0:05:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,view the view of yourself a view of God\Nthe level emotional level and a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.47,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated scale\Nand the process going on within
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.36,0:05:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.03,0:05:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to move from the lower to the upper\Nmeans to go through
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.00,0:05:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,uh this process.\NSo you can see that despair,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.40,0:05:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,humiliation, blame, all these things,\Ncraving and hate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.44,0:05:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. are amanable to let's say\Nforgiveness is a very powerful one. You
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.03,0:06:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,can always if you're willing forgive\Nanything of anyone and see and you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.75,0:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what Jesus Christ taught the\Nsermon on the mount through forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.96,0:06:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nto move from the bottom of the ladder
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.47,0:06:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,from the move from the bottom from all\Nthese negative emotions. In psychiatry,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.52,0:06:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,these are called the emergency emotions.\NEverything from 200 down. And these are
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.91,0:06:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,called the welfare emotions.\NWe know that healing takes place through
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,all these positive emotions. Lovingness,\Nuh willingness, acceptance,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,reason, love, joy, and eventually peace.\NAnd if you keep doing this, you end up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.16,0:06:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with a state of enlightenment. So that's\Njust a quick review for those who are
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.31,0:06:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,not familiar with it. Everybody here is\Ngenerally familiar with it. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.84,0:07:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we have just a few review slides.\NWe'll do them successfively this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.59,0:07:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,morning. What's the next one?\NOh,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.47,0:07:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Oh, yes. Those are the\Nhigher states. The other u the other
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.72,0:07:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,scale only goes up to 600. Uh but these\Nare the higher states from 600 on up to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.72,0:07:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,a thousand from eight from 600 up to a\Nthousand. Usually at any one time there
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.63,0:07:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,may be only a two one or two or maybe\Nsometimes even no uh people on the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.16,0:07:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,planet that calibrate 600 over 600 is\Nthe opening of the third eye of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.40,0:07:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha body in which you instantly\Nperceive the difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.96,0:07:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance and essence. behind the\Nappearance you see the essence of a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.59,0:07:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,thing. So and that's called the opening\Nof the third eye of the Buddha body. So
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.75,0:08:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll move on to the next.\NThis is the scale of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,uh energy as consciousness goes up uh\Nthe energy goes up becomes more and more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.24,0:08:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,powerful.\NSo one person
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.80,0:08:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,one person at a very high level of\Nconsciousness can actually
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.24,0:08:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalance all of humanity by the\Nfact that it it the power goes up so
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.12,0:08:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,rapidly. Next, next one.\NThe uh 85% of the world's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.59,0:08:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,population 85% This is the world's\Npopulation. The majority of the world's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.24,0:08:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,population calibrates below 200. The\Nmajority of the world's population,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.80,0:08:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in fact, the number above 200 is\Nminuscule compared to the masses below.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.39,0:08:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So why doesn't society self-destruct?\NBecause the power of these individuals
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.32,0:09:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,here is so enormous that they\Ncounterbalance. Next slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.27,0:09:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That they counterbalance. And this is a\Nclassic
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.00,0:09:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,diagram showing the 15% of the world's\Npopulation that calibrates over 200
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,counterbalances the 85%\Nthat is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But it explains human history. Human\Nhistory. You know, we've had war
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.80,0:09:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,something like 97% of recorded time. And\Nright now there's probably half a dozen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.12,0:09:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,wars. Since I've been on the planet,\Nthere's been a couple of wars all the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.36,0:09:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NI consider war to be a normal state.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're not at war, what's the matter\Nwith you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.68,0:09:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You should be aware about something. I\Nmean, you know. Okay. What's next? And
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.20,0:09:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this is just a a re repetition of the\Nsame concept. But this this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.56,0:10:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,visualization just makes it cement in\Nmemory so you can comprehend
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.48,0:10:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and account for the state of the world.\NOkay. Next
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.39,0:10:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the evolution of consciousness over\Ntime
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.16,0:10:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,um as we see the consciousness was very\Nlow at the time of uh the Buddha. The
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.56,0:10:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of mankind was about\N70. Uh by the time of Jesus Christ it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.64,0:10:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,was about 90. Anyway the consciousness\Nlevel
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.51,0:10:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh very very slowly and then suddenly in\Nthe late 1980s
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.92,0:10:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it suddenly shot up for no apparent\Nreason. the late 1980s, the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.88,0:10:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level of mankind,\Nmankind was at 190 for many centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.36,0:10:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All throughout the Middle Ages,\Nit was at 190. And suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.20,0:10:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in the late 80s, for no apparent reason,\Nnever actually explained. It jumped from
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.80,0:11:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,190 to 204 and then went up to 207 and\Nnow it's back down to 204 again. All
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.68,0:11:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,right, we'll move to the next one. So we\Ncalibrated all the animals on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.88,0:11:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh\Nthis has lots of interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.64,0:11:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,implications.\NUh you see the predatory animals
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.12,0:11:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate all below 200. Below 200 you\Nhave the predatory the uh the predatory
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.07,0:11:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,animals the wolf the these people all\Nlive majority majority not all live by
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.00,0:11:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the sacrificing the life of others from\N200 and up uh and the animal world
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.12,0:11:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes more benign.\NYou get up to the kitty cats, the family
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.32,0:11:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,cat, the family dog, monkeys, gorillas,\Nchimpanzees.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.20,0:11:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oscar the cat is at 250.\NAlex the trained African gray parrot is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.80,0:12:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,at 400. Very famous parrot.\NAnd Koko the trained gorilla at 405.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.48,0:12:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Koko the train gorilla is more conscious\Nand safer to be with than 90% of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.92,0:12:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind.\NCoco is very gentle. We got a picture of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.76,0:12:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco at home holding a kitty. Says,\N"Soft, nice, nice kitty." Soft, nice,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.88,0:12:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,nice kitty.\NI thought that's so cute. The cats purr
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.68,0:12:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dogs wagging tail are now\Nfamous. So, if you're surrounded by
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.60,0:12:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,purring cats and dogs with wagging\Ntails, you're you're in a good place
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.76,0:12:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,already.\NStay off the telephone and you're going
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.88,0:12:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a good day.\NStay off the blogger the blogger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.51,0:12:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,machine.\NAll right. Now, what's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.60,0:12:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes. The great books of the western\Nworld. Uh this may sound academic, but
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.63,0:13:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it is of enormous uh importance in\Ntoday's world. uh
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.63,0:13:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatness of western civilization\Nwas was built. This is the intellectual
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.76,0:13:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,structure of the basis of western\Ncivilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.04,0:13:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see it calibrates in the\Nprimarily in the in the high 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.51,0:13:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the reason, logic, scient\Nscience, scientific proof,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.36,0:13:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,uh all the great philosophers from Plato\Nuh on down to current times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.20,0:13:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the great books of the western\Nworld. It was compiled at the University
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.68,0:13:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of Chicago by somebody whose name I\Nalways forget. And uh the thing that's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.00,0:13:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,important about it is you get that the\N400s are the intellect and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.72,0:14:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See there's there's faith and then\Nthere's reason. And faith needs to be
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.39,0:14:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,enforced by reason and the two should be\Nmutually reinforcing. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.92,0:14:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, the thing the implication\Nfor today's society because we're going
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.07,0:14:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to be looking at the world today is you\Nsee they are all in the 400s. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.51,0:14:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all very very high. Uh Dante however is\Nat 505. A few others are Augustine five
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.27,0:14:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,over 500.\NDarwin at 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.56,0:14:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you see angles at 200\Nand uh Markx I don't know where he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's Markx\Ndoesn't belong on the list. Got put in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.68,0:14:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there because of the importance of his\Nwork, social importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.00,0:14:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now the problem in society is\Num what I would call cultural Marxism
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.60,0:15:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,perpetrator victim\Nprojected onto everything that you see
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.24,0:15:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world. So that you can take\Nanybody and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.04,0:15:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,superimpose\Nan interpretation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.60,0:15:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of victim and perpetrator.\NAnd we'll see that later when we get to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.27,0:15:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,things that are more current. Okay. The\Nnext thing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.83,0:15:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nhow a thing comes about
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.92,0:15:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the lectures we we we point out\Nreemphasize
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.92,0:15:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is nothing causing anything\Nelse. There's no cause for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.63,0:15:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the origin of it\Nbut there is no cause. In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.32,0:15:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the phenomena that you see, the mind\Ntends to put it in a linear
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.83,0:15:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,uh scientific causality, Newtonian\Ncausality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.12,0:15:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, everything is occurring\Nspontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.04,0:16:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is autonomous and occurring\Nof itself. Nothing is being caused by
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.95,0:16:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,anything else.\NLet's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.32,0:16:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just spoke was the truth resist.\NNothing is causing anything else.
