Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.96,0:44:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,discern essence. The first time in\Nhistory man can discern the essence and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.28,0:44:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of a thing uh without having\Nit impaired. There is rest internal and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.59,0:44:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,rest externa. Rest interna is as Renee\NDeart said the world as it looks to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.59,0:44:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Rest externa is the world the way it is.\NAnd Socrates of course uh pointed out
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.56,0:44:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that man man\Nuh doesn't see truth. He sees his own
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.40,0:44:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,projections projected onto the world.\NWhat he considers to be the good is what
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.44,0:45:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,he projects onto the world as good. And\Nin more recent times uh the book glamour
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.11,0:45:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,explains it. Uh glamour means that the\Nattractiveness of what you desire in the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.24,0:45:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,world you think is intrinsic to what\Nwhat it is you desire
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.07,0:45:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,new elephant or whatever.\NBut the glamour and attractiveness of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.20,0:45:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that elephant is that you've projected\Ngreat worth and value and desiraability
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.00,0:45:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on the elephant. Although a trained\Nelephant will cost you a couple million.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.20,0:45:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, where would you keep it? I\Ndon't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.96,0:45:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So\Nwe have discussed you know considerably
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.00,0:45:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,relativism versus absolutism.\NThe truth is what it is irrespective of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.35,0:45:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,what you think about it. Uh all right.\NSo that is a different viewpoint that is
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.07,0:46:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this particular absolutism will\Neventually take you to God. If you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.48,0:46:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,follow\Nthe absolute truth, if if every decision
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.28,0:46:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,tree, every decision tree you come to,\Nyou choose that which calibrates the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.64,0:46:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,highest, eventually you will arrive at\Ndivinity. Eventually all roads will lead
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.11,0:46:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to God. And that's why the atheist\Ncannot do consciousness calibration.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.56,0:46:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some well-known professors and all who\Npoo pooed it. And I couldn't understand
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.00,0:46:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,how could how they couldn't get it to\Nwork
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.20,0:46:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're into alternative\Nmedicine and all that kind of stuff. And
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.92,0:46:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then I found out it's because they're\Natheists. So if you negate the very
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.44,0:46:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,source and reality of truth itself which\Nis a divine
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.00,0:46:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,quality of divinity\Nthen you disenfranchise yourself from
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.35,0:46:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the fruits and the rewards\Nof adhering to truth and the source of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.92,0:47:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,truth as divinity.\NAll right. So we'll go to the next. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.28,0:47:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The carnival of the isms.\NUh communism and Marxism. Of course we
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.20,0:47:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,are very familiar. We've already pointed\Nout paternalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.00,0:47:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You get what you deserve through you\Nyour own self uh uh discipline and
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.16,0:47:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,maternalism that everybody deserves to\Nlive because they are born a human in
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.68,0:47:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,our society. Then you have the various\Nlevels of in infantilism
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.16,0:47:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,which are really um\Nnarcissism.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.11,0:47:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Infantilism is really narcissism\Nand narcissism is really a form of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.56,0:47:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,infantilism\Nin which you just think about me and
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.92,0:47:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody is supposed to teach to to\Ntreat your inner feelings as though they
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.04,0:47:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,are precious.\NNobody's supposed to hurt your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.56,0:48:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as long as we don't hurt anybody's\Nfeelings, we're okay. Except that's
